    • consumeCustomData

      public void consumeCustomData​(int target)
      Description copied from interface: TextureData
      Uploads the pixel data to the OpenGL ES texture. The caller must bind an OpenGL ES texture. A call to TextureData.prepare() must precede a call to this method. Any internal data structures created in TextureData.prepare() should be disposed of here.
      Specified by:
      consumeCustomData in interface TextureData
